                <h1>Unraveling the Themes in "The Yellow Wallpaper"</h1>
                <p>"The Yellow Wallpaper" explores themes of mental illness, gender roles, and the oppression of women. The story's wallpaper symbolizes the protagonist's entrapment and quest for identity. Her descent into madness reflects societal constraints on women's autonomy, illustrating the struggle for self-expression against patriarchal forces.</p>
